description:
Define and validate all server‚Üíclient message schemas.

**Research Reference:** research/2026-01-12-json-schema-websocket-validation.md

**Acceptance Criteria:**

1. Define all server‚Üíclient message schemas in TypeBox (12 types):
   - room:joined {playerId}
   - player:move {players: [{id, position, velocity, health, ...}]}
   - projectile:spawn {id, ownerId, position, velocity}
   - projectile:destroy {id}
   - weapon:state {currentAmmo, maxAmmo, isReloading, canShoot}
   - shoot:failed {reason}
   - player:damaged {victimId, attackerId, damage, newHealth, projectileId}
   - hit:confirmed {victimId, damage, projectileId}
   - player:death {victimId, attackerId}
   - player:kill_credit {killerId, victimId, killerKills, killerXP}
   - player:respawn {playerId, position, health}
   - match:timer {remainingSeconds}
   - match:ended {winners, finalScores, reason}
   - weapon:spawned {crates: [{id, position, weaponType, isAvailable}]}
   - weapon:pickup_confirmed {playerId, crateId, weaponType, nextRespawnTime}
   - weapon:respawned {crateId, weaponType, position}

2. Add validation before server broadcast:
   - Validate outgoing messages in broadcast_helper.go
   - Development-only validation (skip in production for performance)

3. Update client handlers to use typed data:
   - GameSceneEventHandlers.ts uses generated types
   - Remove manual type casting

4. CI validation:
   - Verify client and server schemas match
   - Fail build on schema drift

**Technical Notes:**
- This completes the type-safe event system
- Future weapon messages will follow this pattern
- Enables Story 3.8 (Shared Config) to build on this infrastructure

